How does Python manage memory? Explain the concept of reference counting and garbage collection.
In summary, Python manages memory automatically using reference counting as the primary mechanism and garbage collection to handle cyclic references. 

This combination ensures efficient memory usage and frees developers from manual memory management tasks.

Reference counting is a simple and efficient garbage collection strategy used by Python. It works by keeping track of the number of references to an object. When an object's reference count reaches zero, the object is no longer needed and can be safely deallocated from memory.

